Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Remove and discard any large ribs from @kale{4%ounce}.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain. Keep empty pot handy for step 5.

While pasta cooks, heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in large pan over medium-high heat. Add kale and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with half the @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in pan used for kale over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Return pot used for pasta to medium-high heat. Stir in @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Bring to a simmer; cook for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} and @butter{2%tablespoon} until smooth.

Stir kale and drained penne into pot with sauce. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Slice chicken crosswise. Divide pasta between #bowls{} and top with chicken. Serve.

> For cream sauce, cut top off carton to open fully and transfer contents, using a spoon or spatula to scrape sauce from carton sides.

> If needed, add reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until everything is coated in a creamy sauce.

> Alternatively, stir chicken into pasta before plating, adding more pasta cooking water if necessary.